properties.description: Maximum number of redirects to follow when executing commands across the cluster.

properties.name: common.redis.jedis.pool.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the pool. Enabled automatically if "commons-pool2" is available. With Jedis, pooling is implicitly enabled in sentinel mode and this setting only applies to single node setup.

properties.name: common.redis.jedis.pool.max-active
properties.description: Maximum number of connections that can be allocated by the pool at a given time. Use a negative value for no limit.

properties.name: common.redis.jedis.pool.max-idle
properties.description: Maximum number of "idle" connections in the pool. Use a negative value to indicate an unlimited number of idle connections.

properties.name: common.redis.jedis.pool.max-wait
properties.description: Maximum amount of time a connection allocation should block before throwing an exception when the pool is exhausted. Use a negative value to block indefinitely.

properties.name: common.redis.jedis.pool.min-idle
properties.description: Target for the minimum number of idle connections to maintain in the pool. This setting only has an effect if both it and time between eviction runs are positive.

properties.name: common.redis.jedis.pool.time-between-eviction-runs
properties.description: Time between runs of the idle object evictor thread. When positive, the idle object evictor thread starts, otherwise no idle object eviction is performed.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.cluster.refresh.adaptive
properties.description: Whether adaptive topology refreshing using all available refresh triggers should be used.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.cluster.refresh.dynamic-refresh-sources
properties.description: Whether to discover and query all cluster nodes for obtaining the cluster topology. When set to false, only the initial seed nodes are used as sources for topology discovery.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.cluster.refresh.period
properties.description: Cluster topology refresh period.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.pool.enabled

properties.description: Maximum number of "idle" connections in the pool. Use a negative value to indicate an unlimited number of idle connections.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.pool.max-wait
properties.description: Maximum amount of time a connection allocation should block before throwing an exception when the pool is exhausted. Use a negative value to block indefinitely.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.pool.min-idle
properties.description: Target for the minimum number of idle connections to maintain in the pool. This setting only has an effect if both it and time between eviction runs are positive.

properties.name: common.redis.lettuce.pool.time-between-eviction-runs
properties.description: Time between runs of the idle object evictor thread. When positive, the idle object evictor thread starts, otherwise no idle object eviction is performed.
